    <questiontext format="markdown">
      <text>**31.4 E1 Bisection Method**

The function 

{@f(x)=fn@}

has a single zero. Find two consecutive integers \\\(a\\\) and \\\(b\\\) which bracket the zero of \\\(f\\\).


\\\(a, b=\\\) [[input:S_a]], [[input:S_b]] 

[[validation:S_a]] [[validation:S_b]] 

[[feedback:ab]]

Perform one iteration of the bisection method. What is the new bracketing interval?

\\\(a, b=\\\) [[input:S_a1]], [[input:S_b1]] 

[[validation:S_a1]] [[validation:S_b1]] 

[[feedback:ab1]]</text>
    </questiontext>
